## System policy rules
### This is an example set of rules that point to chrome/chromium and firefox's policy files.
### It logs every instance a process attempts to write to the directories/files, or modify their attributes.
### To enable them, uncomment the lines of the policy files you have on your system.

#-w /etc/opt/chrome/ -p wa -k chrome-policy

#-w /etc/chromium/ -p wa -k chromium-policy

#-w /etc/chromium-browser/ -p wa -k chromium-policy

#-w /usr/lib64/firefox/distribution/policies.json -p wa -k firefox-policy
#-w /usr/lib64/firefox/defaults/pref/autoconfig.js -p wa -k firefox-policy
#-w /usr/lib64/firefox/firefox.cfg -p wa -k firefox-policy

#-w /usr/lib/firefox/distribution/policies.json -p wa -k firefox-policy
#-w /usr/lib/firefox/defaults/pref/autoconfig.js -p wa -k firefox-policy
#-w /usr/lib/firefox/firefox.cfg -p wa -k firefox-policy

#-w /usr/lib/firefox-esr/distribution/policies.json -p wa -k firefox-policy
#-w /usr/lib/firefox-esr/defaults/pref/autoconfig.js -p wa -k firefox-policy
#-w /usr/lib/firefox-esr/firefox-esr.cfg -p wa -k firefox-policy
